{"title_page": "Esra Sibel Tezkan", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Esra Sibel Tezkan\n| fullname = \n| image = EsraSibelTezkan (1).JPG\n| caption = Esra Sibel Tezkan playing for [[Turkey women's national football team|Turkey women's national]] (April 2016)\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1993|02|23}}\n| birth_place = [[Bremerhaven]], Germany\n| height = \n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub = [[1. FFC Bergisch Gladbach 2009|Bergisch Gladbach 09]]\n| clubnumber = \n| youthyears1 = 2004\u20132008\n| youthclubs1 = Fortuna K\u00f6ln\n| years1 = 2008\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen (women)|Bayer 04 Leverkusen]]\n| caps1 = \n| goals1 = \n| years2 = 2013\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[1. FFC Bergisch Gladbach 2009|Bergisch Gladbach 09]]\n| caps2 = \n| goals2 = \n| nationalyears1 = 2010\n| nationalteam1 = [[Turkey women's national under-17 football team|Turkey U-17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 4\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2010\u20132012\n| nationalteam2 = [[Turkey women's national under-19 football team|Turkey U-19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 13\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2014\n| nationalteam3 = [[Turkey women's national under-21 football team|Turkey U-21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 1\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Turkey women's national football team|Turkey]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 5\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = May 3, 2015\n| nationalteam-update = April 8, 2016\n}}\n\n'''Esra Sibel Tezkan''' (born February 23, 1993) is a [[Turks in Germany|Turkish-German]] female [[Association football|football]] [[defender (association football)|defender]] currently playing in the German Women's Regional League of the Middle Rhine for 1. FFC Bergisch Gladbach 2009. She is part of the Turkey women's national football team.\n\n==Family life==\nEsra Sibel Tezkan was born to a Turkish immigrant father and a German mother in [[Bremerhaven]], Germany on February 23, 1993. She was supported in playing football by her father, a professor of [[geophysics]] at the [[University of Cologne]], who is an amateur footballer as well. She has two older brothers, the one being footballer and the other performing athletics.<ref name=\"tff1\"/>\n\n==Playing career==\nHer father took Esra Sibel to football matches always he was playing. So, she got interested in football at her very early age. She began playing football with boys since no girls were available to play with. At age five, her father registered Esra Sibel to a club, where she had to play again with boys. After six years when she became eleven, she was transferred by the women's side of [[SC Fortuna K\u00f6ln]] in her hometown, where she started to play football among girls. She finds that her time of playing with boys had contributed very positive on her strength.<ref name=\"tff1\"/>\n\n==Club==\nAfter playing four years for SC Fortuna K\u00f6ln, Tezkan moved at age fifteen to [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen (women)|Bayer 04 Leverkusen]].<ref name=\"tff1\"/><ref name=\"b04l1\"/><ref name=\"b04l2\"/>\n\nIn the 2013\u201314 season, she signed for [[1. FFC Bergisch Gladbach 2009]], where she currently plays in the [[Frauen-Mittelrheinliga]] (Women's League of the [[Middle Rhine]]).<ref name=\"fupa1\"/><ref name=\"bg1\"/>\n\n==International==\nTezkan was discovered for the Turkey women's national team by [[Bilgin Defterli]], a Turkish women's footballer, who moved from Turkey to Germany for her professional football career only.<ref name=\"tff1\"/>\n\nEsra Sibel Tezkan was admitted to the [[Turkey women's national under-17 football team|Turkey girls' U-17]] team debuting in the International Women's Football Friendship Tournament against Bulgaria on June 27, 2010. She capped four times in total for the Turkey girls' U-17 team.<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\nOn September 11, 2010, she appeared first time in the [[Turkey women's national under-19 football team|Turkey women's U-19]] team playing at the [[2011 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship First qualifying round#Group 9|2011 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship First qualifying round \u2013 Group 9]] match against Romania.<ref name=\"tff1\"/><ref name=\"b04l2\"/> She took part at the [[2011 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship Second qualifying round#Group 3|2011 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship Second qualifying round \u2013 Group 3]], 2011 Kuban Spring Tournament and [[2012 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship#Group A|2012 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship \u2013 Group A]] matches.<ref name=\"h1\"/><ref name=\"iha1\"/> She capped in thirteen games of the Turkey women's U-19 team.<ref name=\"tff0\"/>\n\nTezkan played once for the [[Turkey women's national under-21 football team|Turkey women's U-21]] team in the friendly match against Belgium on November 26, 2014.<ref name=\"tff0\"/><ref name=\"tg1\"/>\n\nOn February 26, 2015, she took part at the friendly game of the [[Turkey women's national football team|Turkey women's]] team against [[Georgia women's national football team|Georgia]].<ref name=\"tff0\"/><ref name=\"amks\"/> Tezkan played at the [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 qualifying Group 5]] matches for Turkeywomen's national.<ref name=\"h2\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"tff0\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=526&kisiId=1343642 |publisher=Turkish Football Federation |title=Player Details \u2013 Esra Sibel Tezkan |date= |accessdate=2015-06-03 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"fupa1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.fupa.net/spieler/sibel-tetzkan-289881.html |publisher=[[K\u00f6lner Stadt-Anzeiger]] |title=Pers\u00f6nliche Daten: Sibel Tetzkan |language=German |accessdate=2015-06-03 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"tff1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=286&ftxtID=15773 |publisher=T\u00fcrkiye Futbol Federasyonu |title=Sibel Tezkan: Profes\u00f6r baban\u0131n futbolcu k\u0131z\u0131 |date=2012-08-01 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2015-06-03 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"amks\">{{cite news |url=http://a