at Again Tour 2020\n|-\n| 4 December \n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Pete Tong|Pete Tong & The Heritage Orchestra]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Ibiza Classics\n|-\n| 5 December \n|-\n| 9 December  \n| Elton John\n| Farewell Yellow Brick Road\n|-\n|10 December \n|JLS\n|Beat Again Tour 2020\n|-\n| 14 December \n| Elton John\n| Farewell Yellow Brick Road\n|-\n|15 December \n|JLS\n|Beat Again Tour 2020\n|-\n| 16 December  \n| rowspan=\"2\"|Elton John\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Farewell Yellow Brick Road\n|-\n| 17 December  \n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:O2 Arena}}\n[[Category:British entertainment-related lists|Entertainment events at O2 Arena]]\n[[Category:Entertainment events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Events in London]]\n[[Category:Lists of events by venue]]\n[[Category:Lists of events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:London-related lists|Entertainment events at O2 Arena]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{EngvarB|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{cleanup|date=November 2016|reason=There are too many citations for certain events, keeping only 1 reliable source for each event will suffice.}}\n\nSince opening in 2007, [[The O2 Arena]] has hosted hundreds of concerts from UK and international superstars. It was named the ''World's Best Venue'' by Pollstar in 2009. It has been named as the busiest indoor arena in the world with over 1,819,487 tickets sold in 2015 alone.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pollstarpro.com/files/charts2015/2015YearEndWorldwideTicketSalesTop200ArenaVenues.pdf|title=2015 Year End Worldwide Ticket Sales Top 200 Arena Venues|access-date=25 September 2016|archive-url=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20160517203229/http://www.pollstarpro.com/files/charts2015/2015YearEndWorldwideTicketSalesTop200ArenaVenues.pdf|archive-date=17 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nBelow is a list of artists that have performed at the arena since its opening in 2007.\n\n==2007 \u2013 2010==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=October 2016}}\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n\n|-\n\n! colspan=\"3\"|Entertainment events held at the O2 Arena\n\n|-\n! width=100| Date\n\n! width=150| Artists\n\n! width=300| Events\n\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#ddd;\"\n! colspan=\"3\"|'''2007'''\n\n|-\n| 23 June\n\n| [[Dermot O'Leary]] (Host)<br>[[Philip Anschutz|Anschutz]]<br>[[Peter Kay]]<br>[[Tom Jones (singer)|Tom Jones]]<br>[[Kaiser Chiefs]]<br>[[Basement Jaxx]]<br>[[Snow Patrol]]\n| Opening Ceremony of the O2 Arena\n|-\n| 24 June\n| [[Bon Jovi]]\n| [[Lost Highway (Bon Jovi album)|Lost Highway]] Promotional Show\n|-\n| 28 June\n| [[Snow Patrol]]\n| [[Eyes Open Tour]]\n|-\n| 4 July\n| rowspan=5| [[Justin Timberlake]]\n| rowspan=5| [[FutureSex/LoveShow]]\n\n|-\n| 5 July\n|-\n| 7 July\n|-\n| 8 July\n|-\n\n| 10 July\n\n|-\n\n| 18 July\n| [[Barbra Streisand]]\n| [[Streisand (concert tour)|Streisand: The Tour]]\n\n|-\n\n| 21 July\n| [[Keane (band)|Keane]]\n| [[Under the Iron Sea Tour]]\n\n|-\n| 22 July\n| rowspan=2| [[Barbra Streisand]]\n| rowspan=2| Streisand: The Tour\n|-\n| 25 July\n|-\n| 1 August\n| rowspan=9|[[Prince (musician)|Prince]]\n| rowspan=9| [[The Earth Tour: 21 Nights in London|Earth Tour]]\n\n|-\n\n| 3 August\n\n|-\n\n| 4 August\n\n|-\n\n| 7 August\n\n|-\n\n| 10 August\n\n|-\n\n| 11 August\n\n|-\n\n| 14 August\n\n|-\n\n| 17 August\n\n|-\n\n| 18 August\n\n|-\n| 21 August\n| rowspan=2| [[The Rolling Stones]]\n| rowspan=2| [[A Bigger Bang Tour]]\n\n|-\n| 23 August\n\n|-\n| 24 August\n| rowspan=2| [[Prince (musician)|Prince]]\n| rowspan=2| [[The Earth Tour: 21 Nights in London|Earth Tour]]\n\n|-\n\n| 25 August\n\n|-\n| 26 August\n| [[The Rolling Stones]]\n| [[A Bigger Bang Tour]]\n|-\n| 28 August\n| rowspan=3| [[Prince (musician)|Prince]]\n| rowspan=3| [[The Earth Tour: 21 Nights in London|Earth Tour]]\n\n|-\n\n| 31 August\n\n|-\n\n| 1 September\n\n|-\n| 5 September\n| [[Elton John]] \n| [[The Red Piano#The Red Piano: Live in Europe|The Red Piano Tour]]\n\n|-\n| 6 September\n| rowspan=7| [